lity that handles several products used to protect public health by treating water, wastewater, swimming pools and other uses.  This site manufactures sodium hypochlorite (also known as bleach).  Chlorine is part of this manufacturing process.  Chlorine is the only chemical covered by Process Safety Management and Risk Management Plan for this facility.  



Prevention Program:  Accident prevention is achieved through safe handling procedures and safety systems that properly protect chlorine during receipt, storage and use.  This starts with DOT FRA approved 90-ton railcars that are robustly designed to contain chlorine through expected conditions during transport, storage and unloading.  It continues through having employees trained in proper handling procedures and equipping them with equipment to safely transfer chemicals during manufacture.  



Hawkins accident prevention program includes:

1. Procedures and training for handling chlorine during manufacturing of sodium hypochlorite;

2. Implement safety systems to manage risks identified during process hazard analysis;

3. Conduct necessary plant maintenance and inspections to ensure equipment is in good working order;

4. Vendor provided DOT approved railcars;

5. Adhere to OSHA workplace safety regulations;

6. Follow Chlorine Institute standards.

7. Members in good standings with National Association of Chemical Distributors



5-year Accident History:  There has not been an accident involving chlorine at this facility in the last 5 years.



Emergency Response:  In the event of a maintenance issue with chlorine equipment/railcar, employees are trained on how to detect the source of the issue and take appropriate action such as closing or tightening a valve.  If an accidental release should occur, this facility has a trained on-site hazmat team including proper equipment (SCBA and C-kits) to respond.  This facility also conducts annual meetings and training sessions with the local emergency planning committ
